{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:51:01.249Z","taskId":"KB-002","text":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me compile my review.\n\n## Plan Review: Step 5 — Developer Tooling Configuration\n\n### Verdict: APPROVE\n\n### Summary\nThe step's checkboxes are well-defined and will produce working Prettier and ESLint configuration. The installed dependency versions (ESLint 10.4, Prettier 3.8, typescript-eslint 8.59)","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:51:03.601Z","taskId":"KB-002","text":" are compatible with each other and with the flat config format specified in the plan. Two items deserve attention but neither blocks approval.\n\n### Issues Found\n\n1. **[Severity: minor]** — ESLint will not process `.astro` files. The dependencies include `prettier-plugin-astro` but **no** `eslint-plugin-astro`. The ESLint flat config with `@typescript-eslint/parser` will handle `.ts`","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:51:05.797Z","taskId":"KB-002","text":" and `.js`/`.mjs` files, but `.astro` files will either be silently ignored or cause parse errors. This is acceptable for the scaffold — Astro files can be linted later — but the `npx eslint .` validation checkbox should either (a) configure `ignores` for `*.astro` in the flat config, or (b) explicitly note that `.astro` files are out of scope","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:51:07.174Z","taskId":"KB-002","text":" for ESLint. Without an ignore pattern, ESLint's default file traversal may attempt to parse `.astro` files and fail.\n\n2. **[Severity: minor]** — The `overrides` array for `*.astro` files in `.prettierrc` is mentioned but not fully specified. `prettier-plugin-astro` auto-registers for `.astro` files when listed in `plugins`, so an explicit `overrides","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:51:09.777Z","taskId":"KB-002","text":"` entry is only needed if you want different formatting options for Astro files. The checkbox should clarify that the override's purpose is just to ensure the parser is set to `astro`, or the override can be omitted since the plugin handles it. Either way, it won't cause a failure.\n\n### Suggestions\n\n- **ESLint `.astro` ignore**: Add an `ignores` or file-specific config in `eslint.config.m","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:51:11.582Z","taskId":"KB-002","text":"js` that either ignores `**/*.astro` or notes it explicitly. Example:\n  ```js\n  export default [\n    { ignores: ['**/*.astro'] },\n    // ... rest of config\n  ];\n  ```\n  This prevents the `npx eslint .` check from hitting parse errors on Astro component files.\n\n- **Consider `eslint-plugin-astro`**: If Astro file linting is desired now or in","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:51:13.573Z","taskId":"KB-002","text":" a downstream task, add `eslint-plugin-astro` to devDependencies. For KB-002 scope, ignoring `.astro` files is fine.\n\n- **Prettier `overrides` example**: A concrete shape for the overrides would remove ambiguity:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"overrides\": [\n      {\n        \"files\": [\"*.astro\"],\n        \"options\": { \"parser\": \"astro\" }\n      }\n    ]\n","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:51:15.049Z","taskId":"KB-002","text":"  }\n  ```\n\n- **ESLint flat config shape**: The plan says \"flat config format for ESLint v9+\" but doesn't specify which rule sets to enable. With `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin` v8, the recommended approach is:\n  ```js\n  import tseslint from '@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin';\n  import tsParser from '@typescript-eslint/parser';\n  \n  export default [\n    {","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:51:16.857Z","taskId":"KB-002","text":" files: ['**/*.{ts,js,mjs}'], languageOptions: { parser: tsParser } },\n    { plugins: { '@typescript-eslint': tseslint }, rules: { ... } },\n  ];\n  ```\n  The `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin` v8 exports a `configs.recommended` flat-config-ready object that can be spread. The worker should be aware of this pattern since ESLint v10 is installed.","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
